//Default configurations (Remove in production)
sc.hadoopConfiguration.set("fs.s3n.awsAccessKeyId", System.getenv("AWS_ID"))
sc.hadoopConfiguration.set("fs.s3n.awsSecretAccessKey", System.getenv("AWS_SECRET"))
val pathToCdrs = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/cdrs/africell-raw/20200403_1[4-6].csv"
val pathToTowers = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/TOWERS/africell/sites_2020-07-03.csv"
val pathToOutput = "s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/AGGEGATED_CDRS/africell/stops"

import org.apache.spark.sql.functions.{split, lit, window, concat, unix_timestamp, to_timestamp, date_format}
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
//import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window
import spark.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.storage.StorageLevel

 val calls = spark.read.format("csv")
    .option("header","false")
    .option("inferSchema", "true")
    .load(pathToCdrs)
    .withColumnRenamed("_c0", "antenna_id")
    .withColumnRenamed("_c1", "time")
    .withColumnRenamed("_c2", "direction")
    .withColumnRenamed("_c3", "source")
    .withColumn("subscriber", col("source"))
    .withColumnRenamed("_c4", "target")
    .withColumnRenamed("_c5", "duration")
    .withColumn("site_id", substring(col("antenna_id"), 0, 4))
    .withColumn("call_datetime", to_timestamp($"time"))
    .withColumn("call_date", to_date($"call_datetime"))
    .withColumn("end_time",  to_timestamp(unix_timestamp($"call_datetime") + ($"duration")))
    

val cells = spark.read.format("csv")
  .option("header", true)
  .option("inferSchema", true)
  .load(pathToTowers)
  .withColumnRenamed("New_Dist", "locality")
  .withColumnRenamed("CI", "cell_id")

cells.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)
cells.createOrReplaceTempView("cells")

calls.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)
calls.createOrReplaceTempView("calls")

/** 3. Generate All Stops
// Window over the user
// sortby time
// generate index => called event_id
// Aggregation function will create a list of stops
// groupby anetnna_id
*/

/** Specs for window function
 * userSpec :=  this will run our aggregation + analytic function on the key (subscrber, call_date)
 * userSiteSpec :=  this will run our aggregation + analytic function on the key (subscriber, call_date, site_id)
 * eventSiteSpec :=  this will run our aggregation + analytic function on the key (subscrber, call_date, group)
 * @param group  the stops ids 
 * @param event_id the index for row in `userSpec`
 * @param difference the difference between a rows event_id and the event_id the precedes it in the window
 * @param diffNotOne boolean representing whether the `difference` is not equal to one. True if not equal to one
 * @param diffValue assigns a 1 where `diffNotOne` is true and 0 otherwise
 * @param group cumulative sum of the `diffValue` in the specified window
 * @param stop_id gets the minimum event_id over the apppropriate window (eventSiteSpec)
 * 
 * 
 */ 
val userSpec = Window.partitionBy("subscriber", "call_date").orderBy("call_datetime")
val userSiteSpec = Window.partitionBy("subscriber", "call_date", "site_id").orderBy("call_datetime")
val eventSiteSpec = Window.partitionBy("subscriber", "call_date", "group").orderBy("call_datetime")
//val summSpec = Window.partitionBy("subscriber","site_id","stop_id").orderBy("call_datetime")

val stops = calls
                    .withColumn("site_count", count("site_id").over(userSiteSpec))
                    .filter(col("site_count") > 1)
                    .withColumn("event_id", row_number.over(userSpec))
                    .withColumn("difference", $"event_id" - when((lag("event_id", 1).over(userSiteSpec)).isNull, $"event_id").otherwise(lag("event_id", 1).over(userSiteSpec)))
                   .withColumn("diffNotOne", ($"event_id" - when((lag("event_id", 1).over(userSiteSpec)).isNull, $"event_id").otherwise(lag("event_id", 1).over(userSiteSpec)))!== 1)
                   .withColumn("diffValue", when(col("diffNotOne") === true, 1).otherwise(0))
                   .withColumn("group", sum(col("diffValue")).over(userSiteSpec.rangeBetween(Window.unboundedPreceding, 0)))
                   .withColumn("stop_id", min(col("event_id")).over(eventSiteSpec))
                   // group by the subscriber, site_id and the stop id
                   .groupBy("subscriber","site_id","stop_id")
                   // collect the minimum and maximum start and end time
                   .agg(min(col("call_datetime")).alias("start_time"), max(col("end_time")).alias("end_time"))
                   //calculates the duration between the start and end times.
                   .withColumn("duration", unix_timestamp(col("end_time")) - unix_timestamp(col("start_time")))

// Registers a temporary view for the stops dataframe
stops.createOrReplaceTempView("stops")
